@startuml agentclass-propagation
' How an AgentClass or ModelProvider edit reaches Agents and AgentTasks: the three buckets.
' Source of truth: docs/src/controller/change-propagation.md
!include _style.puml

start
:AgentClass or ModelProvider\nspec edit;<<$ctrlBg>>
:EnqueueRequestsFromMapFunc re-queues
every referencing workload.
AgentClass watch: indexed on
agentClassRef.name. ModelProvider
watch: indexed on providerRef.name;

if (workload kind?) then (Agent)

  if (does the change EXCLUDE\nthe Agent's stored spec?) then (yes)
    :Bucket 2: degrade-when-irreconcilable
    phase=Degraded, record preDegradedPhase
    reason names the mismatch;<<$ctrlBg>>
    note right
      Excluded: image not in
      allowedImages, provider not in
      allowedProviders, provider
      allowedNamespaces drops this
      namespace, persistence, or
      hibernation. Reason is one of
      ClassConstraintViolation,
      PersistenceNotAllowed,
      HibernationNotAllowed,
      HibernationRequiresPersistence.
      The Pod is not recreated.
    end note
    stop
  else (no)
  endif

  if (Pod-spec hash differs in a\nreplacement-triggering field?\nimage, resources, command,\nargs, env, provider wiring) then (no)
    :Bucket 3: routing-concern change.
    Gateway CRD and Secret watches
    pick it up. No Agent-side effect,
    no Pod-level transition;<<$gwBg>>
    stop
  else (yes)
  endif

  :Bucket 1: recreate-and-clamp;<<$agentBg>>
  if (phase == Hibernated?) then (yes)
    :defer to the next wake,\nwhich provisions from the\nalready-clamped spec;
    stop
  else (no)
  endif
  :phase=Provisioning;
  :delete the Pod (SIGTERM, honoring\nterminationGracePeriodSeconds);
  :create the new Pod from the clamped\nspec. PVC, Service, Certificate kept;
  :phase=Running once the Pod is Ready;
  stop

else (AgentTask)

  if (task phase?) then (terminal:\nSucceeded, Failed,\nTimedOut)
    :ignore class drift,
    proceed to TTL cleanup;<<$mutedBg>>
    stop
  else (non-terminal)
  endif

  if (in flight?\nRunning or\nProvisioning) then (yes)
    :run to completion under the class
    snapshot taken at task-Pod creation;<<$agentBg>>
    stop
  else (no: Failed, retrying\nunder backoffLimit)
  endif

  :increment status.retries, then re-validate\nthe stored spec against the new class;
  if (still admitted?) then (no)
    :phase=Failed
    reason=ClassConstraintViolation;<<$mutedBg>>
    stop
  else (yes)
    :provision the retry Pod\nunder the new invariants;
    stop
  endif

endif

note right
  Bucket membership depends on
  whether the change EXCLUDES a
  stored spec value, not on the
  field's nominal category. That is
  why a restrictive allowedNamespaces
  edit is bucket 2, even though
  allowedNamespaces is listed under
  bucket 3. So the exclusion test
  runs first.
  ....
  AgentTask has no Degraded phase.
  Where an Agent degrades, the task
  uses Failed with the same reason.
end note

@enduml
